On each liquidity provider we conduct a risk assessment at inception and ongoing thereafter on a yearly basis, or ad-hoc in the case of any screening hits or adverse media, or regulatory sanctions, or changes to the ownership or control structure, or changes to the licensee.  The following information and/or documentation is collected and/or checked/screened on the liquidity provider to conduct the Risk Assessment: liquidity provider’s name (including screening), registered address, physical address (including jurisdictional area), licence, authorised/regulated by, website, directors (including screening), shareholders (including screening), regulatory/law enforcements, sanctions, terms and conditions.  Other information and/or documentation is collected on a case-by-case basis and/or in accordance with our findings in conducting the risk assessments. 

The assessments and other due diligence (including independent checks) are maintained by the Company for the duration of the business relationship and five (5) years following termination (this was our reply as part of the post visit letter for the compliance inspection held in 2022 (DB Path: Deriv_Compliance_DIEL/MFSA/Onsite visits & Offsite inspections/2022/20220202 - Compliance Inspection/MFSA OUT/20220725 - Post visit response)

