If no major incidents occurred in the period, confirm this on the quarterly compliance report. 

Process: When a major ICT-related incident occurs, conduct and document a Post-Incident Review covering:

a) Responsiveness

- Assess promptness in responding to security alerts.
- Evaluate timeliness in determining incident impact and severity.

b) Forensic Analysis

- Assess whether forensic analysis was performed (where appropriate).
- Evaluate quality and speed of analysis.

c) Incident Escalation

- Assess the effectiveness of escalation procedures within the entity.
- Check timeliness and appropriateness of escalation decisions.

d) Communication

- Review effectiveness of internal communication (management, teams).
- Review effectiveness of external communication (clients, regulators, partners).$X$,$X$If major incident occurred, perform a post-incident analysis.$X$,'TO_DO'::"TaskStatus",'MEDIUM'::"RiskRating",'QUARTERLY'::"Frequency",$X$Q4$X$,'2025-10-01'::date,FALSE,TRUE,TRUE,$X$https://app.clickup.com/t/86c5kqeaw$X$,(SELECT id FROM "MonitoringArea" WHERE name = $X$Incidents and Cyber Threats$X$ LIMIT 1),(SELECT id FROM "TaskType" WHERE name = $X$Desk-Based Review$X$ LIMIT 1),$X$9ebc7955-ab3a-f0e2-ca2c-c563bba055ed$X$,$X$fe60240d-fe69-d709-8bd8-64e69988849a$X$,(SELECT id FROM "Entity" WHERE code = 'DIEL' LIMIT 1),(SELECT id FROM "Team" WHERE name = $X$Compliance Regulatory$X$ LIMIT 1),NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NOW(),NOW());
