The monitoring consists of the following checks:

1) Checks on Accounts Marked as Internal Clients:
For internal accounts, email domain verification ensures association with an official company domain, followed by a deposit review to confirm transactions were processed by the accounts team, with proper documentation collected before finalizing the review.

2) Checks on Accounts not Marked as Internal Clients:
For non-internal accounts, a detailed review of email and account details is conducted to identify company-related domains and ensure consistency. Mislabelled test accounts are corrected, followed by domain and balance verification, aligning with internal account procedures.

3) Checks on potential Withdrawals by staff members;
 As part of the withdrawal review, accounts are checked for withdrawal activity, ensuring transactions were processed by the payments team and not by staff members. Any staff-initiated withdrawals undergo a compliance review to prevent personal gain and uphold operational integrity.$X$,$X$To ensure the check is done accordingly. If any discrepancies are identified, the appropriate remediation plans shall be put in place.$X$,'TO_DO'::"TaskStatus",'LOW'::"RiskRating",'QUARTERLY'::"Frequency",$X$Q1$X$,'2025-03-31'::date,FALSE,TRUE,TRUE,$X$https://app.clickup.com/t/8677m57nz$X$,(SELECT id FROM "MonitoringArea" WHERE name = $X$Staff Dealing$X$ LIMIT 1),(SELECT id FROM "TaskType" WHERE name = $X$Desk-Based Review$X$ LIMIT 1),$X$78e804ac-d97a-8503-c92a-be30d85469b7$X$,$X$43010521-28ac-9e15-a2cb-ed21ed392bf1$X$,(SELECT id FROM "Entity" WHERE code = 'DIEL' LIMIT 1),(SELECT id FROM "Team" WHERE name = $X$Compliance Regulatory$X$ LIMIT 1),$X$3c05b744-b25b-1ded-2ab6-3e47006def2e$X$,0,4,0,NOW(),NOW());

